<plot>Three student leaders in the 1980's protests that helped restore democracy to Chile, were children in 1973 when Pinochet lead the coup that killed two of their fathers. Through archival footage and contemporary reflections this film documents the journey each has taken from shock, to silence, to protest, to relief and now, as they reach 40, to reentering public life trying again to transform Chilean society.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?433489</url></doc>
